      "id": 355138,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Among the many examples of S<sub>N</sub>1 reactions that occur with incomplete racemization, the optically pure tosylate of 2,2-dimethyl-1-phenyl-1-propanol ([<i>α</i>]<sub>D</sub> = –30.3) gives the corresponding acetate ([<i>α</i>]<sub>D</sub> = +5.3) when heated in acetic acid. If complete inversion had occurred, the optically pure acetate would have had [<i>α</i>]<sub>D</sub> = +53.6. What percentage racemization and what percentage inversion occurred in this reaction?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcVlUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ff7dbaa0b1c071b7bc2b48f2dc516d874f947945/OChem_11_04_007.jpg\" alt=\"A reaction of tosylate of 2,2-dimethyl-1-phenyl-1-propanol (alpha D equals negative 30.3) with acetic acid forms acetate (observed alpha D equals plus 5.3) and T o s O H.\">",
      "answers": [],
